{
  "query": "What is the evidence for the success of interventions like translocation and rehabilitation for Hawaiian monk seals in the North Pacific Ocean?",
  "relevant_summary": "Studies found that 50-83% of translocated Hawaiian monk seal pups survived for at least one year. Translocated seal pups had similar survival rates to non-translocated pups born at release sites, and greater survival rates than non-translocated pups remaining at the original site. Translocated pups exhibited similar dispersal times to non-translocated seal pups born at release sites. More than a quarter of translocated Hawaiian monk seals reproduced after translocation combined with other survival interventions. More than a quarter of rehabilitated and released Hawaiian monk seals successfully reproduced. More than a quarter of seals survived after translocation when implemented along with at least seven other interventions to enhance survival.",
  "action_ids": [
    "2930",
    "2925"
  ]
}

